item.title: Embassies help expats respect Anzac Day
item.description: Australian high commissions and embassies around the world have taken to social media platforms to enable expats commemorate Anzac Day.

item.title: SA resident honours family’s service
item.description: As Lois Strick stood on her driveway holding a candle at dawn, she said having a strong family history of soldiers was the reason Anzac Day was so special to her.

item.title: Rescue for Aussies stranded in Sth America
item.description: More than 150 Australians who've been stranded in South America since the coronavirus outbreak are being brought home on a rescue flight, with one of the pilots paying tribute to his World War Two veteran grandfather on Anzac Day.

item.title: Qld shows respect at home on Anzac Day
item.description: Queenslanders have paid their respects to diggers past and present during a very different Anzac Day.

item.title: Anzac Day marked in spirit amid isolation
item.description: A far-from-traditional Anzac Day marked in isolation and in spirit has added new meaning to our most sacred day.

item.title: Perth man critical after housemate attack
item.description: A man in his late 20s is fighting for his life in hospital after he was allegedly attacked by his housemate in Perth.

item.title: Tenth virus death in Tasmania
item.description: A 90-year-old man has become the tenth person to die from coronavirus in Tasmania.

item.title: Kanye West officially a billionaire
item.description: Kanye West is officially a billionaire, according to Forbes magazine.

item.title: Victorians mark Anzac Day at home
item.description: There was no usual dawn service, march or even two-up this Anzac Day, but Victorians made sure it wasn't forgotten.

item.title: NSW man ‘joined terror org Al-Nusra Front’
item.description: A Sydney man has been charged after allegedly fighting for an al-Qaeda-linked Syrian terrorist group "for months at a time" in 2012 and 2013.
